==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Good-humored
<hw>Good`-hu"mored</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a
cheerful spirit and demeanor; cheerful; good-tempered. See
<er>Good-natured</er>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposed to please.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> amiable, agreeable, good-humored, likable,
likeable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Good-humoredly</ent>⟦br⟧
